Here in Bosnia, police are preparing for curfew. We are really trying our best to delay this.

So basically, this is a small town called Brod o  border with Croatia. For every person that comes in Bosnia & Herzegovina from Croatia (or any other European country) will be kept in these tents for 14 days. Apparently it doesn't matter if you are healthy or with symptoms you'll simple go in there. So, I was thinking if one person is asymptomatic and others are healthy, won't they all be infected within 14 days and be realesed to spread out the infection? The government has given the rules for citizens of B&H to keep distance of at least 1 meter, to wash your hands regularly, to stay at home, etc. But there is no 1 meter between these beds, there isn't even a toilet out there.
